reviewText: As a huge fan of Justin Timberlake, I try to buy any memorabilia that I can come across. I have many DVD sets of him- this one is an "unauthorized film" so he, nor his team, had any part in creating this movie. Sometimes those types of movies are fun to watch; however, this particular one was very amateur. It had no new footage and included more flashing photos than actual film. I love anything with JT, but this DVD did not live up to par.
Great addition to my music collection.

This movie is terrible. Don't waste your money on it. All it contains is 3 interviews that you can watch on YouTube. No new information. The voice over (which sounds like a computer reading) gives little tidbits about him but nothing you wouldn't already know.

The cover of this dvd makes it seem like it's put out by Justin Timberlake's "camp", but you can tell right away that it's not. Luckily it was cheap, or I'd be mad that I bought it. It has a few different clips of shows he appeared on, which you can look up on youtube. I had already seen all of them but one. Disappointed for sure.
This is not an original JT Production. DO NOT BUY. On this DVD you will only find stolen YouTube videos.

Can you give 0 stars!!?!? This should be illegal, clips stolen from the internet and an illiterate voice over who can't read her script!!  I want my money back!!!  Amazon should screen these things!! DO NOT BUY!!
Do not buy. Save your $8. A bunch of youtube interviews put on a DVD. Unauthorized biography. Choppy and crappy editing. Worst thing I have ever bought.
